27/02/2004
BELGRADE, Serbia-Montenegro -- Federal Foreign Minister Goran Svilanovic is urging the new Serbian government to co-operate on war crimes. On Thursday (26 February), he called on the new cabinet to talk to indicted army and police officers, as their surrender should be arranged as soon as possible. Svilanovic, who is also the head of the federal Council for Co-operation with the Tribunal, said that co-operation is imperative for the sake of Euro-integration. (B92, BBC, Beta, Tanjug - 16/02/04)
